Hello Jon,
Election day is over. In January, America will swear in President-elect Trump and
a Republican Congress.
As your Representative and a member of House leadership, I want to make clear
my commitment to you: building an economy where everyone has a fair shot
at success — good pay and secure benefits; affordable housing, health care,
and child care; and the guarantee of a hard-earned, dignified retirement.
I will extend the hand of bipartisanship to anyone willing to improve the
lives of everyday Americans, and will fight any attempt to drain the wages of
working people into the pockets of billionaires. I will use every tool at my disposal
to defend Americans’ fundamental freedoms, including the right to make health
care decisions in consultation with your family, your doctors, and your faith — not
with politicians.
There is a lot of work ahead of us. I want to hear from you:
WHAT ARE YOU MOST
CONCERNED ABOUT?
From: "Congresswoman Katherine Clark"<MA05KCIMA@mail.house.gov>
Subject: Moving Forward
 

Please know that I will never lose sight of our shared values and will always work
to advance America’s promise of opportunity and freedom for all.
Sincerely, 
Congresswoman Katherine Clark
Democratic Whip
*It is my job to listen to Massachusetts families and my constituents — please take my survey to let me know your views and opt-in to my email newsletter so you can
recieve updates on my work in Washington. You can also subscribe or unsubscribe by clicking the links. If you'd like to send me a longer message with your opinion,
please go to my website, where you can also request casework help, learn about new legislation, and get information about resources available to you.
